WEBVTT

00:01.430 --> 00:02.988
*

00:10.070 --> 00:11.207
I love it!

00:18.080 --> 00:20.048
It's over there. Let's go.

00:27.090 --> 00:28.079
You should try one.

00:42.870 --> 00:45.065
*

00:53.720 --> 00:55.119
MAN:
Oh, my gosh, look!

00:55.150 --> 00:57.380
That's that boxer,
Johnny D'Amato!

00:59.360 --> 01:01.282
WOMAN:
Someone, call 911!

01:01.320 --> 01:03.185
Somebody help him! Johnny!
MAN: Call 911!

01:03.230 --> 01:06.222
*

01:10.700 --> 01:12.167
MAN:
25 bucks is a steal.

01:12.200 --> 01:13.792
I mean, look at the set list.

01:13.840 --> 01:16.434
You get "Nobody Weird Like Me,"
"Subway to Venus,"

01:16.470 --> 01:18.802
"Hollywood," "Higher Ground,"
"Out in LA."

01:18.840 --> 01:21.536
I mean, come on, it's a piece
of Chili Pepper history.

01:21.580 --> 01:24.606
Recorded in town
over at the 7 Club.

01:24.650 --> 01:26.777
No. It wasn't.

01:26.820 --> 01:28.344
I was at that show.

01:28.380 --> 01:30.245
Saturday, July 21, 1990.

01:30.290 --> 01:32.315
First time I wore Doc Martens.

01:32.360 --> 01:33.418
And the set list was,

01:33.460 --> 01:35.109
"Pretty Little Ditty,"
"Out in LA,"

01:35.160 --> 01:36.787
"Higher Ground,"
"Knock Me Down," "Backwoods,"

01:36.830 --> 01:39.298
"Nobody Weird Like Me,"
and the encore was

01:39.330 --> 01:42.561
a particularly awesome
cover of "Dr. Funkenstein."

01:42.600 --> 01:44.227
That is nothing more
than a mix tape,

01:44.270 --> 01:45.498
not worth more than a dollar.

01:45.530 --> 01:47.191
You calling me a fraud?

01:47.240 --> 01:48.798
Yeah.

01:48.840 --> 01:50.467
Oh, either that, or you're
a total amateur. You choose.

01:50.510 --> 01:52.808
Hey, Al. On my way.

01:54.340 --> 01:56.399
Hey.

01:56.450 --> 01:57.599
What's going on?

01:57.650 --> 01:59.345
Vic's Johnny D'Amato.

01:59.380 --> 02:00.574
The boxer?

02:00.620 --> 02:02.884
Yeah. Are you a fan?

02:02.920 --> 02:04.239
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentleman,

02:04.290 --> 02:06.315
Johnny D'Amato,
aka "The Face..."

02:06.360 --> 02:10.148
Yeah. I-I just sat a
few rows away from him

02:10.190 --> 02:11.748
recently at the
Pacquiao fight.

02:11.790 --> 02:13.428
You were at that fight?
Yeah.

02:13.460 --> 02:14.859
With who?

02:14.900 --> 02:16.629
Uh, Frank-- Francis.

02:16.670 --> 02:18.194
Oh, Francis.
Yeah.

02:18.230 --> 02:19.663
Mr. Secret Service Guy.

02:19.700 --> 02:21.258
Mr. Secret
Service Guy, yep.

02:21.300 --> 02:22.369
For someone who
protects the preSIdent,

02:22.410 --> 02:24.708
he seems to be spending
a lot of time in New York.

02:24.740 --> 02:27.300
Well, you know,
New York has a lot of...

02:27.340 --> 02:29.308
secrets that need servicing.

02:29.350 --> 02:31.306
Uh-huh.
Hey, guys.

02:31.350 --> 02:33.614
So, Johnny was the guest of
honor at the festival this year.

02:33.650 --> 02:36.346
He was supposed to sign
autographs at 2:00 p.m.,

02:36.390 --> 02:37.789
right after
the grand procession.

02:37.820 --> 02:40.516
But instead,
he showed up at 2:15...

02:40.560 --> 02:42.721
looking like this.
What about a canvass?

02:42.760 --> 02:45.479
Um, UNI's did an initial sweep
before we got here.

02:45.530 --> 02:47.350
They didn't find anything.

02:47.400 --> 02:48.150
AL:
So, Johnny dropped here,

02:48.200 --> 02:49.724
but this isn't
where he was attacked?

02:49.770 --> 02:51.692
Any idea where
the primary crime scene is?

02:51.730 --> 02:54.335
MURRAY: Nope. CSU couldn't
track the blood trail

02:54.370 --> 02:55.632
much further
than a few yards.

02:55.670 --> 02:57.934
Too much foot traffic
from the festival.

02:57.970 --> 02:58.902
AL:
Anything else?

02:58.940 --> 03:00.271
MURRAY:
The last thing I have

03:00.310 --> 03:02.346
is from Johnny's driver,
Moses Perriman.

03:02.380 --> 03:05.440
Mr. Perriman says he picked up
Johnny at his loft on Church,

03:05.480 --> 03:06.879
and then dropped him
at the corner of

03:06.920 --> 03:08.717
Broadway and Walker
at 1300 hours.

03:08.750 --> 03:10.945
That's at least
ten blocks from here.

03:10.990 --> 03:12.457
Driver know where
Johnny was headed?

03:12.490 --> 03:14.412
No, but as far as
I can tell,

03:14.460 --> 03:16.348
Moses was the last person
to see him alive.

03:16.390 --> 03:19.393
And, yeah, I got Jay
to follow up with him.

03:19.430 --> 03:21.421
All right, pull all the security
footage from this area.

03:21.460 --> 03:22.529
Maybe we'll get luclq.

03:29.840 --> 03:32.479
AL: He sure was a hero
to these folks.

03:32.510 --> 03:35.274
Not if they saw
his last fight.

03:35.310 --> 03:38.507
Word on the street is,
Johnny threw it.

03:38.550 --> 03:40.711
That would piss off
a lot of people.

04:00.440 --> 04:01.998
AL:
So, if Carrie's right

04:02.040 --> 04:03.337
and Johnny threw the fight,

04:03.370 --> 04:05.361
who do we think
that would piss off?

04:05.410 --> 04:06.399
Everybody.

04:06.440 --> 04:07.668
We're talking, managers,

04:07.710 --> 04:09.029
promoters, gamblers,
all of them.

04:09.080 --> 04:10.570
So, let's get
a list together and...

04:10.610 --> 04:12.817
Holy crap, Al.
That's Andre Kade.

04:12.850 --> 04:14.875
The rapper.
You know...

04:14.920 --> 04:17.616
"I know I'm no psychic, but
I know that you like it..."

04:17.650 --> 04:18.685
Okay, stop that.

04:18.720 --> 04:20.051
He's also Johnny's manager,

04:20.090 --> 04:23.287
which puts him
at the top of our list.

04:28.760 --> 04:30.068
Listen, I'm sorry
about the weapons ban.

04:30.100 --> 04:32.295
Ah, E-dawg, you know
I hate having Mr. Parker

04:32.340 --> 04:33.364
have to give up his gun.

04:33.400 --> 04:34.765
Yeah, I can't allow it
in Major Crimes.

04:34.800 --> 04:36.062
I'm sorry, AK.

04:36.100 --> 04:38.432
No, you're gonna be sorry
if it goes missing.

04:38.470 --> 04:40.836
That Beretta 92FS is worth
more than you make in a year.

04:40.880 --> 04:42.302
Luckily, I married rich.

04:43.450 --> 04:44.872
AK, this is

04:44.910 --> 04:45.899
Lieutenant A! Burns.

04:45.950 --> 04:48.316
AK has donated $100,000

04:48.350 --> 04:49.647
to find Johnny's killer.

04:49.690 --> 04:51.840
That's right.
Consider it a bounty.

04:51.890 --> 04:53.812
Dead or alive kind of deal?

04:53.860 --> 04:56.658
No. I mean,
whatever helps.

04:56.690 --> 04:58.419
Johnny was
important to me.

04:58.460 --> 05:00.621
AK's been his manager
for two years.

05:00.660 --> 05:02.662
No, I've been a fan
for even longer.

05:02.700 --> 05:05.021
That kid didn't know
what he had or how to market it.

05:05.070 --> 05:07.595
He was losing millions,
so I reached out.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.335
Who was handling him before?

05:09.370 --> 05:10.359
Nobody.

05:11.540 --> 05:12.507
I mean, he was.

05:12.540 --> 05:14.576
Well, him and that
crusty trainer of his, Casey.

05:14.610 --> 05:16.100
Any idea who'd want Johnny dead

05:16.140 --> 05:18.404
or why anyone
would want to kill him?

05:18.450 --> 05:20.372
AK doesn't know anything.
I've asked him already.

05:20.420 --> 05:22.684
Well, Johnny was
a good guy.

05:22.720 --> 05:23.687
People respected him.

05:23.720 --> 05:26.041
He was a killer in the ring,
but he had a code.

05:26.090 --> 05:28.854
That code include
throwing $10 million bouts?

05:28.890 --> 05:30.949
I heard about that,
but I don't believe it.

05:30.990 --> 05:31.752
Johnny was a true warrior.

05:31.790 --> 05:33.496
All he cared about
was the fight.

05:33.530 --> 05:35.088
No way he dumped it.

05:35.130 --> 05:36.358
Do you need anything
else from me?

05:36.400 --> 05:37.492
No. Thank you, AK.

05:37.530 --> 05:38.599
Where were you this afternoon?

05:39.870 --> 05:41.394
I would've thought
you'd be there

05:41.440 --> 05:42.668
for Johnny at the festival.

05:42.710 --> 05:44.109
Well, I had business in Vegas
over the weekend.

05:44.140 --> 05:46.335
I came over here as soon as
my plane touched down.

05:47.710 --> 05:51.077
All right, so if we're done
with the questions.

05:51.110 --> 05:52.145
You need anything, bro,

05:52.180 --> 05:53.442
call me on my cell.

06:02.160 --> 06:04.128
IIE

06:04.160 --> 06:06.128
We go sailing sometimes.

06:06.160 --> 06:08.128
Those are_ some
very Interesting Circles

06:08.160 --> 06:09.661
you're spinning in, Eliot.

06:09.700 --> 06:11.497
Don't waste your time
being envious of me.

06:11.530 --> 06:14.067
I got the Boxing Commission,
the Italian-American Society

06:14.100 --> 06:15.965
and the world's largest
hip-hop mogul on my ass,

06:16.000 --> 06:18.662
and I haven't had_
my afternoon cappuccmo.

06:18.710 --> 06:20.405
Find the guy who wanted
this kid killed.

06:20.440 --> 06:21.771
Please and thank you.

06:26.980 --> 06:28.948
Oh, what a shame.

06:28.980 --> 06:31.517
I used to love to
watch him move.

06:31.550 --> 06:33.450
You were a fan, too?

06:33.490 --> 06:36.527
Oh, I've been a devotee of
the sweet science for years.

06:36.560 --> 06:38.448
I used to moonlight
as the on-call doctor

06:38.490 --> 06:41.527
for the Golden Gloves when I
was a resident at Beth Israel.

06:41.560 --> 06:43.118
Joe Frazier once
sent me flowers

06:43.170 --> 06:47.095
for resetting his nose
in the middle of a match.

06:47.140 --> 06:48.994
I still miss it.

06:49.040 --> 06:52.498
How does a world champion boxer
end up like this?

06:52.540 --> 06:53.973
I don't know.

06:54.980 --> 06:56.038
Okay.

06:56.080 --> 06:58.002
Cause of death
was asphyxiation.

06:58.050 --> 06:59.608
He choked on his own blood.

06:59.650 --> 07:01.447
It's pretty
straightforward.

07:01.480 --> 07:02.617
The X-rays are useless--

07:02.650 --> 07:05.642
too many breaks
to figure anything out.

07:05.690 --> 07:08.614
I know you want an ID.
on the weapon,

07:08.660 --> 07:11.481
but right now, all I can
say is he was hit with

07:11.530 --> 07:12.758
something.

07:12.800 --> 07:14.449
How's that for being specific?

07:14.500 --> 07:15.558
Not very.

07:15.600 --> 07:16.624
I'm considering,

07:16.670 --> 07:19.559
because most of the bruising
has a circular shape,

07:19.600 --> 07:22.728
that maybe he was hit
with the end of a metal pipe.

07:22.770 --> 07:24.567
Maybe.

07:24.610 --> 07:26.635
I really won't know for sure
until I boil his head.

07:28.640 --> 07:31.108
Oh, I know it sounds awful
when you say it out loud,

07:31.150 --> 07:32.617
but it's what I got to do.

07:33.820 --> 07:35.776
Oh. Right after
my protein bar.

07:35.820 --> 07:37.811
I'm on a new program.

07:40.860 --> 07:42.987
MURRAY: I finally spoke to
Johnny's mother, Maria.

07:43.030 --> 07:44.827
She was getting ready
for the festival

07:44.860 --> 07:46.521
when some uniforms
broke the news.

07:46.560 --> 07:47.857
She's hysterical.

07:47.900 --> 07:50.596
Says she has no idea who
would do this to her son.

07:50.630 --> 07:52.495
She know anything about Johnny
throwing his last fight?

07:52.540 --> 07:53.734
No. She never
saw his fights,

07:53.770 --> 07:55.067
never wanted to know
anything about them.

07:55.100 --> 07:56.601
And as a mother,
I get it.

07:56.640 --> 07:57.709
Does he have
any other family?

07:57.740 --> 07:59.776
Seems there's a father who's
been out of the picture

07:59.810 --> 08:01.277
for years, lives
in Honolulu.

08:01.310 --> 08:02.868
But there is an
older brother, Bobby.

08:02.910 --> 08:04.901
She know where Bobby
might be?
She didn't.

08:04.950 --> 08:06.542
I checked his apartment
and he wasn't there.

08:06.580 --> 08:08.616
Apparently, he works as a day
laborer around the city.

08:08.650 --> 08:10.584
She doesn't know which
site he's working today.

08:10.620 --> 08:12.656
Track him down,
we got to talk to him.
Yeah.

08:13.720 --> 08:15.813
So, Eliot knows AK?

08:15.860 --> 08:17.680
Sailing buddies.

08:17.730 --> 08:19.948
Wow.
Mm.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.251
Okay, anyways,

08:21.300 --> 08:23.188
I was doing a little research
into Johnny D'Amato,

08:23.230 --> 08:25.528
because I'm more of
a Mixed Martial Arts guy.

08:25.570 --> 08:27.538
AK may not believe
that Johnny took a dive,

08:27.570 --> 08:28.639
but he is in the minority.

08:28.670 --> 08:29.659
Check it out.

08:29.710 --> 08:31.564
Facebook,
Twitter, Tumblr--

08:31.610 --> 08:33.532
they're all saying
the same thing:

08:33.580 --> 08:35.002
something was up
with that fight.

08:35.040 --> 08:36.200
Now, take a look

08:36.240 --> 08:37.070
at round three.

08:44.250 --> 08:46.081
See, Johnny just
drops his gloves.

08:46.120 --> 08:47.610
I mean, come on,
who does that?

08:47.660 --> 08:49.582
Sure doesn't look like
the Johnny D'Amato

08:49.630 --> 08:51.621
I'm used to seeing.

08:54.100 --> 08:55.988
Was he as good
as they say?
Oh, yeah.

08:56.030 --> 08:58.169
He was like the Italian-
American Sugar Ray Leonard.

08:58.200 --> 08:59.599
Oh, you mean,
the lightweight?

08:59.640 --> 09:01.232
Lightweight? Jay,

09:01.270 --> 09:02.737
as a New Yorker,
as a sports fan,

09:02.770 --> 09:04.135
you need to appreciate.

09:04.170 --> 09:05.967
Sugar Ray Leonard
is a legend.

09:06.010 --> 09:08.001
Well, do you appreciate
Anderson "The Spider" Silva?

09:08.040 --> 09:09.644
Or Fedor Emelianenko?

09:09.680 --> 09:10.601
No.
Oh, get out of here.

09:10.650 --> 09:12.345
And they were the greatest
fighters of all time

09:12.380 --> 09:13.779
in my sport,
so we're even.

09:13.820 --> 09:15.014
No, we're not even.

09:15.050 --> 09:16.688
Boxing is an art.

09:16.720 --> 09:18.210
That stuff you watch
is a blood sport.

09:18.250 --> 09:20.218
See, you say that
like it's a bad thing.

09:22.260 --> 09:25.024
So, if Johnny took a dive,
why'd he do it?

09:25.060 --> 09:27.699
Maybe someone ordered him to.

09:27.730 --> 09:29.891
Like somebody owned him.

09:29.930 --> 09:30.897
Could be.

09:30.930 --> 09:33.137
Check with
Organized Crime.

09:33.170 --> 09:35.866
See if you can find a
financial link to anybody

09:35.900 --> 09:37.629
who may have had Johnny
under their thumb.

09:37.670 --> 09:39.638
Go back as far as
you have to.

09:39.680 --> 09:40.476
No problem.

09:41.840 --> 09:44.377
You know who'd be
really pissed off

09:44.410 --> 09:47.072
if Johnny actually
threw that fight?

09:47.120 --> 09:49.918
His trainer,
Casey McGraw.

09:49.950 --> 09:51.349
Makes sense.

09:51.390 --> 09:53.085
In addition to
a couple of battery raps

09:53.120 --> 09:55.213
he had as a teenager,
look what he did to fighters

09:55.260 --> 09:56.386
who didn't give
a hundred percent.

09:56.420 --> 09:57.887
He broke one guy's arm,

09:57.930 --> 09:59.386
cracked five ribs
on somebody else.

09:59.430 --> 10:00.954
I don't even get why
anybody would train with him.

10:01.000 --> 10:01.819
He was the best.

10:01.860 --> 10:04.624
Fighters thought
he was worth the risk.

10:04.670 --> 10:06.661
But you got to wonder
what Casey would do

10:06.700 --> 10:08.736
if one of his greatest fighters
took a dive.

10:17.450 --> 10:20.044
Everybody loved Johnny.

10:20.080 --> 10:22.719
Nobody wanted
to kill him.

10:22.750 --> 10:24.217
Besides that,
I got nothing to say.

10:24.250 --> 10:25.080
Ah, come on.

10:25.120 --> 10:27.953
Casey, we got so much
to talk about.

10:27.990 --> 10:30.754
Yeah

10:30.790 --> 10:31.757
Well, I don't know.

10:32.900 --> 10:34.151
Like Jack Dempsey,

10:34.200 --> 10:35.155
the "Manassa Mauler."

10:35.200 --> 10:36.758
1920, he was the man.

10:36.800 --> 10:38.119
83 fights,

10:38.170 --> 10:39.797
65 wins, 11 draws,

10:39.840 --> 10:41.967
six losses,
one no contest.

10:42.000 --> 10:45.106
And I'm always up for chatting
about Sugar Ray Robinson,

10:45.140 --> 10:46.778
the original
pound-for-pound king.

10:48.840 --> 10:50.944
Look, we just need

10:50.980 --> 10:53.676
a minute of your time.

10:53.720 --> 10:54.971
ForJohnny.

10:58.920 --> 11:00.785
Take a break!

11:02.830 --> 11:04.957
CASEY: All right,
you've seen my sheet.

11:04.990 --> 11:07.322
Cops aren't
my favorite people.

11:07.360 --> 11:09.351
I got five minutes.
What do you want to know?

11:09.400 --> 11:10.958
What happened
to your hand?

11:11.000 --> 11:12.695
I, uh, split a knuckle.

11:12.740 --> 11:13.695
Part of the job.

11:13.740 --> 11:14.991
AL: Where were you
about 1:00 p.m.?

11:15.040 --> 11:16.905
CASEY:
At home.

11:16.940 --> 11:18.407
Can anybody confirm that?

11:18.440 --> 11:19.998
My cat.

11:20.040 --> 11:22.804
All right,
what's this about?

11:22.850 --> 11:23.976
You think I had
something to do with

11:24.010 --> 11:24.999
what happened to Johnny?

11:26.780 --> 11:29.442
Whoever killed Johnny killed me.

11:29.480 --> 11:31.710
Johnny was the best.

11:31.750 --> 11:33.911
He was my best.

11:33.960 --> 11:36.110
Casey, you hear
what people are saying

11:36.160 --> 11:37.457
about Johnny's last fight?

11:37.490 --> 11:41.256
There's no way he threw it.

11:41.300 --> 11:44.792
I saw those knockdowns, Casey.

11:44.830 --> 11:46.024
It-it didn't look good.

11:46.070 --> 11:50.006
Well, he was distracted
that morning, uh...

11:50.040 --> 11:53.407
riled up, but...
not in a good way.

11:53.440 --> 11:55.032
He say what was bothering him?

11:55.080 --> 11:58.004
No. Johnny... kept it
to himself.

11:58.050 --> 11:59.745
He kept quiet most of the time.

11:59.780 --> 12:01.839
He... just kept it inside,
you know?

12:01.880 --> 12:05.179
But there's no way
he took a dive.

12:05.220 --> 12:07.450
It's not how
I trained him.

12:07.490 --> 12:09.219
He-he wouldn't do that.

12:09.260 --> 12:10.454
Not to me.

12:10.490 --> 12:13.994
You were like
a father to him, huh?

12:14.030 --> 12:16.919
I mean, you took care of him
after his father left.

12:16.970 --> 12:18.961
Yeah, him and his brother both.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.764
I mean, they were like
all the kids around here.

12:21.800 --> 12:24.064
But Johnny, he was...

12:24.110 --> 12:26.499
he was different from the rest.

12:26.540 --> 12:29.134
I mean, I knew he had
that special sauce.

12:29.180 --> 12:31.944
And that face.

12:31.980 --> 12:34.972
Oh, forget about it.

12:35.020 --> 12:37.011
He was a star.

12:39.020 --> 12:40.453
I want to show you something.

12:40.490 --> 12:43.152
Okay, just look at this.

12:46.430 --> 12:48.159
You see that?
Yeah.

12:48.200 --> 12:49.497
Johnny was quick as a rabbit.

12:49.530 --> 12:50.519
That's what he was known for,
"the combination."

12:50.570 --> 12:51.923
There's not many people

12:51.970 --> 12:53.835
can finish a combination
with the same hand.

12:56.600 --> 12:59.501
Right hook, left uppercut,
left cross.

12:59.540 --> 13:01.269
That's not bad.

13:01.310 --> 13:04.040
You want to, uh,
pop your hips at the end.

13:04.080 --> 13:05.968
You'd be surprised
the difference it makes.

13:06.010 --> 13:07.272
Yeah?
Yeah.

13:07.320 --> 13:08.275
Ooh!

13:08.320 --> 13:09.844
Oh.

13:09.890 --> 13:11.881
This one's got
the special sauce, too, huh?

13:11.920 --> 13:14.252
